This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for vehicle re-identification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on comparing different distance metrics and extending the image-to-track process to a track-to-track process, which involves machine learning techniques such as fine-tuning CNNs and evaluating performance metrics, indicating a likelihood of the paper belonging to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
